Hi Team,
i am trying to create a docker image and deploy in cloud as a POC , hence i am looking for a way to test the dashboard locally once i deploy the docker image.
we have this command to test locally --> gulp serve --local true
but for docker we will be executing the command --> docker run -t -p 8088:80 --link hygieia-api -i hygieia-ui:latest

can anyone please let me know how to use test data for UI when API/UI/DB are containerized.

Regards,
vishal
column5: how to test UI locally for docker
column11:
504892573 @vishalbisa Are you using separate mongo service in kubernetes and created dashboarddb in it.
Can you please share some steps which you followed to perform the deployment of hygieia on kubernetes as we are facing issues while deploying on kubernetes. rabindersethi
504970256 Yes I am using separate mongo service and post that I have done a ssh inside the container and created the dashboarddb.
Another method is you need to build and create a docker image from the source code which has the script which creates the dashboard db.

You can choose any of these methods vishalbisa
504998144 @vishalbisa Myself and rabindersethi are working together on this.

As you have mentioned above to use **docker run -t -p 8088:80 --link hygieia-api -i hygieia-ui:latest** to have UI running. 
Per your pervious comment, we have done the same, have separate service for mongo but we still have DB connectivity issue. We took one collector to start with, but none of API, UI and Jenkins aren't working. 

We have created YAMLs to create deployment and service in kubernetes. Could you please share the steps you followed or how you have done the deployment in Kubernetes.  ekta-thakur
505033694 As I said it would be better if we have a screen share session , but I have deployed it manually and not worked on YAMLs to create deployment vishalbisa
505090600 To add above point after deployment of mongo.. expose the service and take the IP address and port no and put it in application.properties file for API n COLLECTOR.
It should work then  vishalbisa

i am not sure from where these parameters are fetching as i dont see those in my properties file.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/16570454/58724123-6a002300-83f9-11e9-8fdd-01dbfdc41d6a.png)

[jenkins.txt](https://github.com/Hygieia/Hygieia/files/3242305/jenkins.txt)

_MONGO_PORT=tcp://db:27017
if [ "$MONGO_PORT" != "" ]; then_

We already have a working setup for Jenkins where we are able to view the builds on the build widget but we are facing issues while trying to get that working for udeploy and Bitbucket(public repo)

we are using 6.2.1 version of udeploy.  HarshitMit

This feature is an alternate solution to HygieiaJenkinsPlugin. An enterprise might restrict installation of Hygieia Jenkins Plungin for a number of reasons - compliance, stability, governance, SOX etc...
HygieiaJenkinsPluginAlt is called by Jenkins pipeline, it capture metrics (same as collected by Hygieia Jenkins plugin)  and push it to Hygieia by calling Hygieia API's to persist data in Hygieia Mongo database. 

Please refer readme document for details.

column2:
Recently, I started a conversation for my opensource contribution in Hygieia project and I was instructed to remove my copyright (the entity I am representing) section from the source code I wanted to contribute.
In this context, I am opening this issue in a hope that we can solidify OSS contribution process for Hygieia project. 
I have explored some other popular opensource project and how they manage OSS contributions. Here I will take the example of Spring Framework and Apple’s Swift project and highlight their OSS contribution process.

- **Spring Framework**: Spring project enforces contributors to sign [Contributor’s License Agreement](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#code-of-conduct) Please see [Pivotal CLA](https://cla.pivotal.io/about) for more details on why this is needed.

- **Swift**: Contributing guide to swift opensource project can be found in [Swift Contribution Guide]( https://swift.org/contributing/#contributing-code)
Swift project maintainers clearly mention list of copyright headers in the [CONTRIBUTORS.txt](https://swift.org/CONTRIBUTORS.txt) file. This file include all the contributors. Please see their license details [Swift License](https://swift.org/community/#license)

These projects protect copyright and make contributors copyright easily traceable.
Looking forward to collaborating and I am happy to provide additional details on this topic(if required).

@Sbrenthughes @tabladrum
column5: Open Source Contribution process for Hygieia project

column2:
I am using Jenkins to display jacaco/junit build data in my Hygieia Dashboard. 
My jenkins build shows the Code Coverage Trend and Test Result Trend. 
My application.properties file is as below:

> dbname=dashboarddb
dbhost=localhost
dbusername=dashboarduser
dbpassword=dbpassword
dbport=27017
dbreplicaset=false
dbhostport=localhost:27017
jenkins-codequality.servers[0]=http://localhost:8080/
jenkins-codequality.cron=0 0/1 * * * *
jenkins-codequality.artifactRegex.junit=TEST-.*\\.xml
jenkins-codequality.artifactRegex.findbugs=findbugsXml.xml
jenkins-codequality.artifactRegex.pmd=pmd.xml
jenkins-codequality.artifactRegex.checkstyle=checkstyle-result.xml
jenkins-codequality.artifactRegex.jacoco=jacoco.xml
server.port=9091 

Post running the collector I could not see any errors but not data is picked either. The dashboard itself if not showing any jobs running 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/24870997/53717220-7833b700-3e7d-11e9-90b0-fd483cf09800.png)

Is it possible to get Junit build data from jenkins to hygieia dashboard?

469419503 @Sathyap3  if this is not a private repo, I would recommend to remove all api tokens and run collector. 
1) delete widget and reconfigure with out api token 
2) remove below props 
`gitlab.apiToken=iN1Lb+dNRqagRq4HUeMfDRnmrDo0j3Ac4kvgHlsLnUx
gitlab.commitThresholdDays=15
gitlab.key=0CaGVCAHikVRH48WKZHpfD7NAQ4ET6T`

if it is private repo, follow these steps 
1) deleted configured widget
2) remove below props 
`gitlab.apiToken=iN1Lb+dNRqagRq4HUeMfDRnmrDo0j3Ac4kvgHlsLnUx
gitlab.commitThresholdDays=15
gitlab.key=0CaGVCAHikVRH48WKZHpfD7NAQ4ET6T`
3) generate personal access token in gitlab -> developer settings -> genereate token 
4) use generated token in prop file as 
gitlab.apiToken= <generated from gitlab
`
5) reconfigure repo widget without apiToken, process will take it from prop file.  If you configure on widget, that will take precedence over prop file. 
6) run collector
 nireeshT

467938990 @shreyamNewt  get latest code and do clean install. We did remove bower config from UI https://github.com/Hygieia/Hygieia/pull/2732, so it is just npm and gulp.  Refer https://github.com/Hygieia/Hygieia/blob/7f4e3597ff65cd015db576125c82d6fbdbbafe3e/pages/hygieia/UI/ui.md for installation steps. 
Recommended to upgrade node version to latest  nireeshT
467989690 If you are stilling having issues, try deleting 'node_modules', 'dist', and 'bower_components' from your UI folder manually. Then try rebuilding. This should force your project to use the latest set of dependencies.

Also make sure you have the latest version of the core downloaded and built (https://github.com/Hygieia/hygieia-core ). 

Let us know if you are still having problems. kheinz04

468004491 We recently updated the project to remove bower so there may be some dependency issues. Try deleting 'node_modules', 'dist', and 'bower_components' from your UI folder manually, then try rebuilding. This should force your project to use the latest set of dependencies. You can also make sure npm is up to date by running 'npm update'.

Also make sure you have the latest version of the core downloaded and built (https://github.com/Hygieia/hygieia-core ).
We recommend having the latest version of node as well.

These were the resolutions to the main issues our team was having after the update. Let us know if you are still having problems after trying these out. kheinz04

column2:
So, I have been asked to evaluate Hygieia for use with our stack and right away I suspect the Bitbucket cloud connector only supports API v1. I say this based on documentation that refers to the `v1/api`
As well as looking at [The actual code](https://github.com/Hygieia/Hygieia/search?q=DefaultBitbucketCloudClient&unscoped_q=DefaultBitbucketCloudClient)

The whole reason this is an issue is because [bitbucket is discontinuing the 1.0 endpoint in April](https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/bitbucket/deprecation-notice-v1-apis/) and it's significantly different than 2.0 - I know this because I just got done with a lot of integration straddling between them

Also, not directly related but important: BB is deprecating API tokens in favor of OAUTH

https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/bitbucket/bitbucket-api-changes-gdpr/

**My issue:** Am I correct in my assumptions about V2 support for BB?
column5: BB Connector support for BB API 2.0
column11:
498640247 @shishirchaturvedi any thoughts here? rvema
498912542 @chb0github I think you are right. This is the code which fetches commits,
https://github.com/Hygieia/Hygieia/blob/40b4242e2740b3b0bbc4aba4aaabb087e99dcbff/collectors/scm/bitbucket/src/main/java/com/capitalone/dashboard/collector/DefaultBitbucketCloudClient.java#L98
I didn't find `/repositories/` path in the rest API URL. This doesn't match with [BB Rest API v2](https://developer.atlassian.com/bitbucket/api/2/reference/resource/repositories/%7Busername%7D/%7Brepo_slug%7D/commits)
In Hygieia SCM collector, the main mechanism for authenticating REST API is HTTP header authentication. 
I am not using Bitbucket Cloud so I can't test its integration in Hygieia. 
As you are using Bitbucket Cloud so you can take current implementation for Bitbucket Cloud in Hygieia as starting point and can enhance it to support V2 and [Oauth2](https://confluence.atlassian.com/bitbucket/oauth-on-bitbucket-cloud-238027431.html). 
 shishirchaturvedi

** using docker **

> jenkins.niceNames[0]=
> 
> #Determines if build console log is collected - defaults to false
> jenkins.saveLog=true
> 
> #map the entry localhost so URLS in jenkins resolve properly
> #Docker NATs the real host localhost to 10.0.2.2 when running in docker
> #as localhost is stored in the JSON payload from jenkins we need
> #this hack to fix the addresses
> jenkins.dockerLocalHostIP= mirageglobe
465113254 Fixed

**in properties-builder.sh, there is a mistake having it generate "application.properties" when test_script is defined or /config/hygieia-jenkins-build-collector.properties** 

collector should have followed standard properties file "application.properties" rather than jumping between to avoid docker-compose issues

**resolved by placing PROP_FILE /hygieia/config/application.properties in docker-compose.override.yml file when using docker-compose** mirageglobe

462330238 If it wasn’t written to mongo then it wouldn’t have completed successfully. Your api is not pointing to the same db that the collector is pointing at. 

Option 1)
Can you open the build widget and see if there is anything in the drop down? If there isn’t proceed to option 2
Option 2)

column5: standard login and Ldap login in hygieia
column11: 464939070 @vkg1234  standard login is authentication/authorization provided with in Hygieia(i.e sign up users via UI in Hygiea) User data is store in MongoDB connected to Hygieia instance. You can also integrate Hygieia with LDAP (aka SSO) with your organization active directory. Refer https://github.com/Hygieia/Hygieia/issues/1731 for LDAP configuration  nireeshT

column2:
This PR allows the UI to be served from the [Red Hat Software Collections nginx images](https://github.com/sclorg/nginx-container).  These images are not intended to run as a specified UID and as such do not have access to places like `/etc/nginx/conf.d`.

`substitute-nginx-proxy-pass.sh` is placed in `./nginx-start/` at build time to correctly set the API server hostname

`api.conf` is a `proxy_pass` snippet that is placed in `./nginx-default-cfg/` for proper routing to the API server

It is intended to be used in an openshift buildconfig such as:

```yaml
- apiVersion: v1                                                                                                                                                                              
  kind: BuildConfig                                                                                                                                                                           
  metadata:                                                                                                                                                                                   
    creationTimestamp: null                                                                                                                                                                   
    labels:                                                                                                                                                                                   
      app: ${COMPONENT}                                                                                                                                                                       
    name: ${COMPONENT}                                                                                                                                                                        
  spec:                                                                                                                                                                                       
    nodeSelector: null                                                                                                                                                                        
    output:                                                                                                                                                                                   
      to:                                                                                                                                                                                     
        kind: ImageStreamTag                                                                                                                                                                  
        name: ${COMPONENT}:latest                                                                                                                                                             
    postCommit: {}                                                                                                                                                                            
    resources: {}                                                                                                                                                                             
    runPolicy: Serial                                                                                                                                                                         
    source:                                                                                                                                                                                   
      images:                                                                                                                                                                                 
      - as: null                                                                                                                                                                              
        from:                                                                                                                                                                                 
          kind: ImageStreamTag                                                                                                                                                                
          name: build-${COMPONENT}:latest                                                                                                                                                     
        paths:                                                                                                                                                                                
        - destinationDir: .                                                                                                                                                                   
          sourcePath: /opt/app-root/src/dist/.                                                                                                                                                
        - destinationDir: ./nginx-default-cfg                                                                                                                                                 
          sourcePath: /opt/app-root/src/docker/rhel/api.conf                                                                                                                                       
        - destinationDir: ./nginx-start                                                                                                                                                       
          sourcePath: /opt/app-root/src/docker/rhel/substitute-nginx-proxy-pass.sh                                                                                                                 
      type: Image                                                                                                                                                                             
    strategy:                                                                                                                                                                                 
      sourceStrategy:                                                                                                                                                                         
        from:                                                                                                                                                                                 
          kind: ImageStreamTag                                                                                                                                                                
          name: nginx:latest                                                                                                                                                                  
          namespace: openshift                                                                                                                                                                
      type: Source                     
```

461826494 Just an update to help.. it seems that the issue is caused by the npm plugin defined in pom.xml (UI/pom.xml)

I disabled the installation by (frontend-maven-plugin) and manually installed npm/bower/gulp as well as running gulp before mvn clean install package (run in both UI and root)
  <properties>
    <frontend-maven-plugin.skip>true</frontend-maven-plugin.skip>
  </properties>

the issue is noted in the following maven plugin (allowing running executables in maven project)
https://github.com/mojohaus/exec-maven-plugin/issues/111

Problem: node nor bower/gulp is unable to be executed via maven for some reason. manual execution is possible. mirageglobe

column2:
Hello, installed Hygieia as part of a project we have, and the idea is for Hygieia to automatically refresh the build jobs status (successful, failure, unstable and aborted) for all the build jobs run in each of the Jenkins folders/projects.
For ex, we have a Jenkins folder that represents a project in Jenkins, and for that project/folder several jobs run per day (more than 100 sometimes). We need to have all those jobs automatically loaded in Hygieia with their status.
So how can we automatically refresh each Jenkins build job status on Hygieia ? 

We checked that we can add a build widget, and after a new build job is run in Jenkins, we are able to see it listed on Hygieia to add it manually, but first we are adding a single job and second we are doing it manually. We need Hygieia to refresh that status data automatically for each Jenkins run job.

thanks
column5: How to automatically grab new build Jenkins jobs in Hygieia?
column11:
460305381 We have a Hygieia Jenkins Publisher Plugin, you could leverage that. The plugin needs to be installed on all Jenkins masters and that way all the build information can be pushed from Jenkins to Hygieia on a event basis. This will eliminate the need to run Jenkins Collector. Do let me know if you need help. rvema
460307712 Hi rvema, we have the "Hygieia Publisher Plugin" installed in Jenkins, is that the one ?
Description of it: This plugin is publisher that can publish build status to Hygieia Dashboard.

If that's the one, do you have the specific steps to get it worked as you said, instead of using the Hygieia build collector ? 

BTW, we are looking to automatically see on a Hygieia dashboard, all the build jobs that Jenkins is able to push in real time.

Thanks!  manuq21
477776846 https://github.com/Hygieia/Hygieia/blob/gh-pages/pages/hygieia/hygieia-jenkins-plugin/hygieia-jenkins-plugin.md Sbrenthughes

column2:
Looks like you're not using any error-checking in your Java build. This pull requests adds a static analysis tool, [Error Prone](http://errorprone.info), created by Google to find common errors in Java code. For example, running ```mvn compile``` on the following code:
```java
public boolean validate(String s) {
	return s == this.username;
}
```
would identify this error:
```
[ERROR] src/main/java/HelloWorld.java:[17,17] error: [StringEquality] String comparison using reference equality instead of value equality
[ERROR]     (see https://errorprone.info/bugpattern/StringEquality)
```
If you think you might want to try out this plugin, you can just merge this pull request. Please feel free to add any comments below explaining why you did or did not find this recommendation useful.
column5: Error Prone Static Analysis Tool

column2:
Resolves #2577
with help of pull request to [hygieia-core PR-#36](https://github.com/Hygieia/hygieia-core/pull/36)

* When creating code quality collector the name is set to the specified in the `CodeQualityCreateRequest#toolName`.
* If it is not specified, then the default tool name `Sonar` will be kept (to tally with existing collectors)
column5: CodeQuality Collector name can be set using create request

column2:
1. APM (Dynatrace)

As we continue our journey towards continuous delivery we realized that if we can have the performance test results published to Hygieia it will help the teams to review the quality and performance of the code in a single place.

Different teams use different APM solutions out of which the prominent names are Appdynamics, Dynatrace etc. Our use case is dynatrace. Is there any plan to make a widget that will be available on the dashboard to which we can integrate dynatrace results (Performance Test). Is this a capability that is already available ?

2. LogSearch (Splunk)

Is there any plan for Splunk integration to the Hygieia dashboard ? This would be for the feedback on application during a functional/regression or performance test or even after an artifact deployment. The widget in this integration if can check a predefined set of queries on Splunk and upload the results that would be helpful.

Looking forward for the feedback on these queries.
column5: Application performance management & Log Search Integration with Hygieia for Continuous feedback

column2:
Have been tracking down the source of a frustrating issue where Jenkins build collector doesn't seem to respect settings from configuration.

Commented out these lines from the `properties-builder.sh` and it resolved the issue

```
if [ "$TEST_SCRIPT" != "" ]
then
        #for testing locally
        PROP_FILE=application.properties
else
	PROP_FILE=config/hygieia-jenkins-build-collector.properties
fi
```

It would seem this would allow for the properties file to be created in the wrong location. Where the config would be written to `config/hygieia-jenkins-build-collector.properties` but the application will be started with 

```
--spring.config.location=$PROP_FILE
```
Where `$PROP_FILE` is provided by the Dockerfile as `ENV PROP_FILE /hygieia/config/application.properties`
column5: Inconsistencies in docker property-builder script causing unexpected failure due to misconfiguration
column11:
456233165 Also noteworthy is that this "local testing" block doesn't appear in all the collectors' `properties-builder.sh`. 

Similar code is found in scripts for xldeploy, appdynamics, and gitlab. I don't use those collectors, but presumably, this problem would exist for those using these collectors with docker-compose. spyoungtech
456245114 Please see MatthewBeasley’s comment here: https://github.com/Hygieia/Hygieia/issues/2489. It describes how to override the properties file. 

But we do need to update the documentation and make it consistent across the collectors. Also, there will be an over haul of the docker setup contributed back to the project soon. So stay tuned.  Sbrenthughes
456246755 Thanks for that link @Sbrenthughes . Looking forward to changes in the docker setup.

I have a couple reservations about overriding the environment variable, particularly because the `PROP_FILE` variable in the shell script can change based on the presence of this `TEST_SCRIPT` environment variable, and will change regardless of what value is supplied in the environment variable.

In other words, I believe these lines in `properties-builder.sh` to be harmful. Yes, one can override the dockerfile default location to accommodate, but that is treating the symptom rather than root cause.

The Dockerfile cmd will always start the app with the location in environment variable; behaves as expected. The properties-builder script will not respect the environment variable, which is the root cause of this issue.

I would suggest that the environment variable be respected in all cases and that instead of using those lines in the shell script... A tester should override the environment variable instead of using a separate variable `TEST_SCRIPT`.

Also weird that I'd need to do this environment variable override for just these few collectors, which is why it seems (in my view) like a bug that should be fixed, rather than documenting a workaround. spyoungtech
457286467 Thanks for your work, @Sbrenthughes .

Agree with @spyoungtech . Which is why I never did the PR for documentation - I felt that it should be fixed rather than workaround documented. 

Glad to see it will be addressed in the Docker setup overhaul.  daniel-ng
457408852 Also noticed that api-audit properties file contains a similar issue. The propfile location is hard-coded:

https://github.com/Hygieia/Hygieia/blob/master/api-audit/docker/properties-builder.sh#L19 spyoungtech

column2:
Resolves https://github.com/Hygieia/Hygieia/issues/2662

This PR adds pull-request data to Bitbucket server collector.
Description of changes,
- Added `com.capitalone.dashboard.collector.PullRequestCollector` which is invoked from `com.capitalone.dashboard.collector.GitCollectorTask`
- Introduced `com.capitalone.dashboard.bitbucketapi` package which contains classes to construct Bitbucket REST API endpoints
- Added `package-info.java` where ever found it missing
- Added Hibernate validator dependency which spring boot was complaining when executing Application class from IDE.
- Added `com.capitalone.dashboard.collector.PageMetadata` which encapsulates Bitbucket Pagination information

cc: @Sbrenthughes @meetgds

Fix grid resizing for the Quality Widget (Static Analysis)
- Added Bootstrap grid layout to the widgets so that they properly resize

Additional addition for adding "No data found" for all widgets where data does not exist.
- Created a directive to determine whether or not a widget is empty
- Check if all values in the widget (passed in through an array) are null, meaning the widget is empty
- Add "No data found" message to the widget to replace empty data

- added comments on how to properly use the "hideEmpty" directive

Small formatting fixes on various widgets (mostly quality and feature)

- Removed "No iterations found" on feature widget and replaced with "No data found" for consistency
- Updated spacing on quality widget so that "No data found" formats match across all tabs

column11:
455247586 Are your others connecting to the admin db as well? Our documentation says to create a new db called dashboarddb  and use that.  Sbrenthughes
456149135 The error seems to indicate it's trying `localhost:27017`. Make sure you're building the container with your properties. If you're using `docker-compose`, there's the `properties-builder.sh` that can configure your collector app.properties based on environment variables. spyoungtech
456242224 @prateekasthana  Check out #2681 -- I discovered a bug that I believe affects a few collectors when configured with docker.

Removing the `if TEST_SCRIPT` code from properties-builder.sh seemed to do the trick for me. spyoungtech
456737966 @spyoungtech Thanks for the help , It resolved the issue .  prateekasthana

I am re-writing JIRA collector for many reasons
1. Simplify code
2. Performance
3. Data correctness

Here is my fork: https://github.com/tabladrum/hygieia-core (little modifications to some models) and https://github.com/tabladrum/Hygieia/tree/master/collectors/feature/jira the collector (work in progress to add good amount of test cases with real data). 

Would love people to take a test drive and provide early feedback.

column11:
453088670 I found the problem. I had set up my widget before I added the key to my 2 property files. This has the effect of not encrypting my credentials. I just had to re-enter my username in the widget settings to make it encrypted properly.

Sorry, I should have looked harder before I opened the ticket.

Now it works. Crozy

column2:
You can reproduce the issue using following steps.

Create a team dashboard with build,deploy, repo widgets
View widget view and ensure data is displayed properly in all widgets
Switch to pipeline view and click on save (not required to add environments)
Switch back to widget view and one widget is (usually build widget) in a not-configured state
Switch to pipeline view and click on configure, save (Save is a must, if you just switch between views this won't happen)
Switch back to widget view, another widget will be in a not-configured state
If you do it several times all widgets will go to not-configured state one by one
column5: Widgets in team dashboard lose data when switching between widget & pipeline views

column5: Jenkins plugin
column11:
451301475 Please post the syntax used for publish step . Since you have enabled the build publish   in global preferences you may remove the publish step from your pipeline code rvema
454194319 Can you remove this publish step and try using the enable publish of build data from Global Settings of Jenkins? Also please ensure that you are running the latest version of API rvema
454757695 Any update on this? rvema
457338256 Thanks @rvema. I've given up on the plugin and went with the collector instead. I also found that the plugin would hold up builds for a very long period of time. I'll close this ticket. nsaud01
459460373 @nsaud01 The jenkins plugin is much lighter, Can you ping me on gitter in private so that I can help with the same? rvema

column2:
Hi,

I need some information about Jenkins code quality collector that can we monitor selenium test result from Jenkins Server (Jenkins is integrated with Selenium).

Please comment on that.
column5: Jenkins code quality collector
column11:
451985805 Can you check the following: https://github.com/Hygieia/Hygieia/issues/1229 Sbrenthughes
453804585 I have gone through that and found that  If your test case results are a cucumber format file, it is supported.
But if I don't have my result in cucumber format then how can I publish my functional test result in Quality Widget.
Do I need to create a custom collector for that ?
@tabladrum Please share your ideas.  anayyadav

column2:
Fix for Sonar api limit to 10000 results. Added max pages to 20 of page size 500. 
This serves as a temporary work around to get max of 10000 records. 
TODO : Add more filters to pull all the projects from Sonar.
column5: Fix for Sonar api limit to 10000 results. Added max pages to 20.

I have started the jenkins-codequality collector with  the following properties file

# Database Name
dbname=dashboarddb

# Database HostName - default is localhost
dbhost=localhost

#Database Port - default is 27017
dbport=27017

# MongoDB replicaset
dbreplicaset=false
dbhostport=[host1:port1,host2:port2,host3:port3]

# Database Username - default is blank
dbusername=dashboarduser

# Database Password - default is blank
dbpassword=dbpassword

# Collector schedule (required)
jenkins-codequality.cron=0 0/1 * * * *

# Collector servers (required) - can be multiple servers
jenkins-codequality.servers[0]=http://172.32.31.208:8080

jenkins-codequality.username=hygjenkins
jenkins-codequality.apiKey=eabbdc4bc13aa4f8009007d696bbb625


# Collector types (not required, but regex should match only the type specified)
jenkins-codequality.artifactRegex.junit=TEST-.*\\.xml
jenkins-codequality.artifactRegex.findbugs=findbugsXml.xml
jenkins-codequality.artifactRegex.pmd=pmd.xml
jenkins-codequality.artifactRegex.checkstyle=checkstyle-result.xml
jenkins-codequality.artifactRegex.jacoco=jacoco.xml

# Collector job depth (required) should be set to at least 1, and more if you use folder jobs, and so on.
jenkins-codequality.jobDepth=4

However in the logs I amd seeing ) jobs fetched and also there is no Job in the dropdown of the Quality widget

column2:
We are publishing deploy environment data to our hygieia stack using the Jenkins plugin. For example:

```
hygieiaDeployPublishStep applicationName: "${APP_NAME}", artifactDirectory: 'dist/', artifactGroup: 'uncontained.io', artifactName: 'index.html', artifactVersion: "${BUILD_NUMBER}-${dev_namespace}", buildStatus: 'Success', environmentName: "${dev_namespace}"
```

However, the team dashboard cannot calculate average lead time because the build and deploy widgets don't have the commit information in them. Is there some way to explicitly send a commit id in the publish steps?

cc: @pcarney8
column5: How to push commit data via DeployPublishStep
column11:
453714133 What version of the plugin are you using? I am thinking the latest solves the global library issue. 

Your deploy steps don’t need commit data. You need to push the artifact data in the build and then once you do your first deploy with that same artifact name, version etc the commit data will automatically sync up. If this isn’t happening you are missing a step. 

Are you using the artifact publish step in your build ? Sbrenthughes
455801928 @etsauer  Sbrenthughes
456162525 @Sbrenthughes yes, I am pushing artifact data, however my 'app' is not a java app, its a static web front-end, so I'm not sure exactly what the "artifact data" should be in that case. etsauer
456163744 Just create an empty zip file and push that via the artifact publisher step, during the build job.  

When you run your deployment job again create that zip file with the same name and push it via the deployment step. It doesn’t actually push the file. It just uses the name on the backend.  Sbrenthughes
457230987 @Sbrenthughes thanks, that fixed it! etsauer
445877090 Another observation.. one of my jenkinsfiles pulls in a global library from github, and the build widget is interpretting that as my source code repository, and pulling commit data from it. It would be nice to have a parameter in the `hygieiaBuildPublishStep` to override that data. etsauer

column2: Hopefully this helps the next person because there's issues with the docs.. From `http://hygieia.github.io/Hygieia/api.html`, - `-v ./mongo:/data/db` won't work because you must first create a `mongo` dir and set `-v $PWD/mongo:/data/db` instead of `-v ./mongo:/data/db` (can't use relative paths) - after exec'ing into the container `docker exec -t -i mongodb bash` , you must run `mongo` before `use dashboarddb` - **Step 3**, which asks you to set Env. Variables, mounting logs file has the same issue as the first point with relative volume paths I'm unable to get past Step 3 .. Getting timeout issues with mongo and other dep issues ![screen shot 2018-11-27 at 5 19 53 pm](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6396257/49115527-0a1d9980-f269-11e8-8afd-9e7bb5041757.png) ![screen shot 2018-11-27 at 5 20 27 pm](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6396257/49115530-0b4ec680-f269-11e8-9d26-8d57dd95a854.png) Please let me know how I can fix this, thanks. I'm using the master branch.
